  "prompt": "How do I open a Snapchat video that won't let me open?",
  "response": "Here are a few troubleshooting steps to try if a Snapchat video won't open:\n\n1. Basic fixes:\n- Close and restart the Snapchat app\n- Force close the app and reopen it\n- Check your internet connection\n- Update the Snapchat app to the latest version\n\n2. Clear app cache:\n- Go to your phone's Settings\n- Find Snapchat in the app list\n- Clear app cache and data\n- Restart the app\n\n3. Device-specific solutions:\n- Restart your phone\n- Check storage space\n- Ensure you have enough memory\n- Delete and reinstall Snapchat\n\n4. Check if the video is still available:\n- Snapchat videos disappear after being viewed\n- The sender might have deleted the snap\n- The snap might have expired\n\n5. Technical issues:\n- Check if the video was sent correctly\n- Ask the sender to resend the snap\n- Make sure your app permissions are enabled\n\nIf none of these work, contact Snapchat support or check their help center for specific troubleshooting.\n\nNote: The exact steps might vary slightly depending on your device and Snapchat version.",
